# Git workflow (Productizer)

Read `specs/git-workflow.html` and skill `productizer-git-workflow` when doing phase or feature work.

## Before creating or editing phase-related files

1. Confirm current branch is `phase/{N}-{slug}` (not `master`).
2. If on `master`, create/checkout the phase branch from latest `master` first:
   `git fetch origin && git checkout master && git pull && git checkout -b phase/N-slug`
3. One roadmap phase per branch and per PR.

## Merging

- All merges to `master` go through pull requests.
- Before opening/updating a PR, agent runs `./scripts/validate-p0.sh` (or phase script) and fixes all FAILs. Use skill `productizer-phase-validate`. Minimize manual user checks.
- Do not force-push `master`.

